HEADWORD: Neoclassic architecture
<hw>Neoclassic architecture</hw>. <def>All that architecture which,
since the beginning of the Italian Renaissance, about 1420, has been
designed with deliberate imitation of Greco-Roman buildings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>neoclassicism</ent>⟦br⟧
